entries.transmission_start: Brother Extok Evin: < The first B-Wings are within firing range of the station. >
entries.transmission_received: Brother Extok Evin: < The station is burning, all payloads delivered! The B-Wings are starting to pull out. >
entries.trans_update: Brother Extok Evin: < The B-Wings have delivered %DI percent of their payloads, hang in there pilot! >
entries.title_d: Some of our bombers have outflanked the Imperial defences but the Empire has picked up on it and is moving to intercept. We're putting you in the middle of their intercept route to prevent them from getting to our bombers.
entries.title: Dathomir system: Cover the B-Wing squads' flank.
entries.quest_reachpoint_d: The Imperial attackers will be passing through these coordinates on their way to intercept our bombers. Proceed to the waypoint right away pilot.
entries.quest_location_d: After our initial failure to eliminate the defense force of the base, the area is now crawling with Imperial fighters. Be prepared for anything!
entries.quest_defendpoint_d: Our last chance pilot. You will come under heavy attack in a few seconds, we're all crossing our fingers that you will do the impossible and prevail.
entries.outofrange_failed: Brother Extok Evin: < Our bomber squadrons are taking casaulties! Abort mission everyone, abort! >
entries.outofrange: Brother Extok Evin: < You're too far away from your assigned sector pilot, get back there immediately! >
entries.mission_complete: Brother Extok Evin: < Splendid job pilot, the bomber squadrons have pulled out safely. Mission complete! >
entries.found_loc: I've assigned you this sector pilot, your squad is spread out covering the nearby areas. Head over there quickly!
entries.first_attack: Here they come pilot and it's not looking good... May the force be with you my friend.
entries.attack_stopped: Tactical Computer: < No more fighter vessels within sensor range. >
entries.attack_notify: Tactical Computer: < Incoming fighter vessels. Scans show weapons armed. >
entries.arrived_at_loc: Patrol this location and don't let anything get past you pilot!
